12namespace v8 {
13namespace internal {
14namespace compiler {
15
16// A helper class to construct inline allocations on the simplified operator
17// level. This keeps track of the effect chain for initial stores on a newly
18// allocated object and also provides helpers for commonly allocated objects.
19class AllocationBuilder final {
20 public:
21 AllocationBuilder(JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* effect,
22 Node* control)
23 : jsgraph_(jsgraph),
24 broker_(broker),
25 allocation_(nullptr),
26 effect_(effect),
27 control_(control) {}
28
29 // Primitive allocation of static size.
30 inline void Allocate(int size,
31 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung,
32 Type type = Type::Any());
33
34 // Primitive store into a field.
35 void Store(const FieldAccess& access, Node* value) {
36 effect_ = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(access), allocation_,
37 value, effect_, control_);
38 }
39
40 // Primitive store into an element.
41 void Store(ElementAccess const& access, Node* index, Node* value) {
42 effect_ = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreElement(access), allocation_,
43 index, value, effect_, control_);
44 }
45
46 // Compound allocation of a context.
47 inline void AllocateContext(int variadic_part_length, MapRef map);
48
49 // Compound allocation of a FixedArray.
50 inline bool CanAllocateArray(
51 int length, MapRef map,
52 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung);
53 inline void AllocateArray(int length, MapRef map,
54 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung);
55
56 // Compound allocation of a SloppyArgumentsElements
57 inline bool CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements(
58 int length, MapRef map,
59 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung);
60 inline void AllocateSloppyArgumentElements(
61 int length, MapRef map,
62 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung);
63
64 // Compound store of a constant into a field.
65 void Store(const FieldAccess& access, ObjectRef value) {
66 Store(access, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(value, broker_));
67 }
68
69 void FinishAndChange(Node* node) {
70 NodeProperties::SetType(allocation_, NodeProperties::GetType(node));
71 node->ReplaceInput(0, allocation_);
72 node->ReplaceInput(1, effect_);
73 node->TrimInputCount(2);
74 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->FinishRegion());
75 }
76
77 Node* Finish() {
78 return graph()->NewNode(common()->FinishRegion(), allocation_, effect_);
79 }
80
81 protected:
82 JSGraph* jsgraph() { return jsgraph_; }
83 Isolate* isolate() const { return jsgraph_->isolate(); }
84 Graph* graph() { return jsgraph_->graph(); }
85 CommonOperatorBuilder* common() { return jsgraph_->common(); }
86 SimplifiedOperatorBuilder* simplified() { return jsgraph_->simplified(); }
87
88 private:
89 JSGraph* const jsgraph_;
90 JSHeapBroker* const broker_;
91 Node* allocation_;
92 Node* effect_;
93 Node* control_;
94};
95
